<h2>Best places to visit in Maldives</h2>

<h3>Male in Maldives</h3>
<p>This island city is filled with spectacular structures like the 17th-century Old Friday Mosque, busy shops like the Male Market, and national monuments like the stately Mulee Aage Palace. This mosque was erected in 1658 and has stood the test of time, retaining its elegance and pleasant spirit.</p>

<h3>Feydhoo in Maldives</h3>
<p>Feydhoo, the Maldives' southernmost inhabited island, is the last sliver of land in the great expanse of the Indian Ocean, making it lonely, calm, and tranquil because few people come this far. Book a Maldives tour package with invisit. </p>

<h3>Hulhumale Island in Maldives</h3>
<p>Explore the abundant aquatic life and magnificent coral reefs with our Maldives vacation packages, which are a diver's dream come true. Take a speedboat across Male's dazzling seas to Hulhumale Island, which has amazing beaches, a glass-topped mosque, a beautiful promenade, and calm, green neighbourhoods. </p>

<h3>Utheemu in Maldives</h3>
<p>For some history, visit the northernmost of the Maldivian island groups, Utheemu, which was formerly home to Sultan Mohammed Thakurufaanu, the leader who drove Portuguese invaders from the islands in the 16th century. </p>

<h3>Maafushi in Maldives</h3>
<p>Your Maldives vacation is incomplete without a visit to the stunning Maafushi Island. Maafushi Island is one of the greatest local Maldivian islands for relaxation, rejuvenation, and escape from the daily grind. This is a lovely corner of the globe to escape to. Stroll along the gorgeous beaches, relax on the Maafushi promenade, and have coffee at the little coffee shops.</p>

<h3>Grand Friday Mosque in Maldives</h3>
<p>The Grand Friday Mosque is another well-known tourist destination to see during Maldives vacations. The mosque is well-known for drawing the attention of many visitors due to its large and soaring golden dome. The mosque is part of the Islamic Center, which is located in the heart of Male. </p>

<h3>Presidential palace in Maldives</h3>
<p>The stunning colonial architecture on display here provides a variety of picturesque backgrounds. Furthermore, this exquisite cottage has been home to about four presidents, and its beauty has not altered.</p>

